---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
	<BaseHead 
		title={`Certified Security Hardware | ${SITE_TITLE}`}
		description="FIPS 140-3 Level 3 certified hardware-encrypted storage devices and security products for enterprise and government use."
	/>
</head>
<body>
	<a href="#main-content" class="skip-to-main">Skip to main content</a>
	<Header />
	<main id="main-content">
		<section class="hero">
			<div class="container">
				<h1>Certified Security Hardware</h1>
				<p class="tagline">High-assurance hardware for data protection and secure communications</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section">
			<div class="container">
				<p>We provide enterprise-grade security hardware that meets stringent protection requirements. All products are carefully evaluated and selected for their certification standards, build quality, and operational security features.</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>Available Hardware</h2>
				
				<div class="card product-card">
					<div class="product-header">
						<h3>iStorage datAshur PRO+C</h3>
						<span class="badge">FIPS 140-3 Level 3 Certified</span>
					</div>
					<p class="product-intro">The datAshur PRO+C is one of the first portable storage devices to achieve FIPS 140-3 Level 3 validation â€” the highest assurance level currently available for commercial removable media. Available for purchase through Hermetrix.</p>
					
					<div class="specs">
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Independent Certification</strong>
							<p>Validated to FIPS 140-3 Level 3, including hardened tamper-resistant construction, role-based authentication, and secure key storage.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Encryption Architecture</strong>
							<p>Full-disk AES-XTS 256-bit hardware encryption performed entirely on the device, ensuring encryption keys never touch a host system.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Tamper-Resistant Electronics</strong>
							<p>Internal components are encapsulated in a protective resin barrier designed to reveal and resist probing, drilling, voltage manipulation, or physical intrusion.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>On-Device PIN Entry</strong>
							<p>Access is controlled through an integrated keypad, preventing keylogging and ensuring authentication occurs before the device connects to any computer.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Brute-Force Protection</strong>
							<p>After a defined number of incorrect PIN attempts, the device cryptographically erases its keys and permanently prevents further access.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>System Compatibility</strong>
							<p>OS-agnostic operation. Works with Windows, macOS, Linux, thin clients, virtualised systems, and embedded devices without drivers or software.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="card product-card">
					<div class="product-header">
						<h3>Google Pixel 7a with GrapheneOS</h3>
						<span class="badge">Hardened Mobile Security</span>
					</div>
					<p class="product-intro">The Google Pixel 7a running GrapheneOS provides a privacy-focused, security-hardened mobile platform. GrapheneOS is a non-profit open-source project focused on privacy and security research and development.</p>
					
					<div class="specs">
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Security-First Operating System</strong>
							<p>GrapheneOS is a privacy and security-focused mobile OS with Android app compatibility, developed as a non-profit open-source project.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Hardware Security Features</strong>
							<p>Pixel 7a includes Google's Titan M2 security chip, verified boot, and hardware-backed keystorage for strong cryptographic protections.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Hardened System Architecture</strong>
							<p>Enhanced exploit mitigations, MAC randomization, hardened memory allocator, and extensive attack surface reduction.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Privacy Protections</strong>
							<p>No Google Play Services by default, network permission toggle, storage scopes, contact scopes, and sensors permission controls.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>App Compatibility</strong>
							<p>Run standard Android apps in a sandboxed environment. Optional sandboxed Google Play Services for app compatibility without system integration.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Pre-Configured & Ready</strong>
							<p>Devices are supplied with GrapheneOS professionally installed, configured for optimal security, and ready for immediate deployment.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section">
			<div class="container text-center">
				<h2>Purchase & Consultation</h2>
				<p>Contact us to purchase the iStorage datAshur PRO+C or Google Pixel 7a with GrapheneOS. We also provide consultation services to help you determine which security hardware best fits your operational requirements, compliance regime, and threat model.</p>
				<div class="cta-buttons">
					<a href="mailto:hello@hermetrix.nz" class="btn primary">Order Products</a>
					<a href="/services" class="btn secondary">View Services</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
	<Footer />

	<style>
		.hero {
			padding: var(--space-3xl) 0 var(--space-2xl);
		}

		.tagline {
			font-size: 1.25rem;
			color: var(--text-secondary);
			margin-top: var(--space-md);
			font-family: var(--font-family-mono);
			text-transform: uppercase;
			letter-spacing: 0.15em;
		}

		.product-card {
			margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
			background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);
			backdrop-filter: blur(5px);
		}

		.product-header {
			display: flex;
			justify-content: space-between;
			align-items: center;
			margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
			flex-wrap: wrap;
			gap: var(--space-md);
		}

		.product-header h3 {
			margin: 0;
			color: var(--text-primary);
			font-weight: 900;
		}

		.badge {
			display: inline-block;
			padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
			background: rgba(255, 0, 255, 0.1);
			border: 2px solid var(--accent-primary);
			border-radius: 6px;
			font-size: 0.75rem;
			font-weight: 700;
			color: var(--accent-primary);
			font-family: var(--font-family-mono);
			text-transform: uppercase;
			letter-spacing: 0.1em;
			box-shadow: 3px 3px 0 rgba(255, 0, 255, 0.2);
			transition: all 0.3s ease;
		}

		.badge:hover {
			transform: translate(-2px, -2px);
			box-shadow: 5px 5px 0 rgba(255, 0, 255, 0.3);
		}

		/* Second product badge - cyan variant */
		.product-card:nth-of-type(2) .badge {
			background: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.1);
			border-color: var(--accent-secondary);
			color: var(--accent-secondary);
			box-shadow: 3px 3px 0 rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.2);
		}

		.product-card:nth-of-type(2) .badge:hover {
			box-shadow: 5px 5px 0 rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.3);
		}

		/* Second product specs - cyan accents */
		.product-card:nth-of-type(2) .spec-item::before {
			background: radial-gradient(circle, var(--electric-blue) 0%, transparent 70%);
		}

		.product-card:nth-of-type(2) .spec-item:hover {
			border-color: var(--accent-tertiary);
			box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 rgba(0, 102, 255, 0.3);
		}

		.product-card:nth-of-type(2) .spec-item strong {
			color: var(--accent-secondary);
		}

		.product-intro {
			font-size: 1.125rem;
			margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
			color: var(--text-secondary);
		}

		.specs {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
			gap: var(--space-lg);
		}

		.spec-item {
			padding: var(--space-lg);
			background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
			backdrop-filter: blur(3px);
			border: 2px solid var(--white);
			border-radius: 6px;
			box-shadow: 4px 4px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
			transition: all 0.3s ease;
			position: relative;
			overflow: hidden;
		}

		.spec-item::before {
			content: '';
			position: absolute;
			top: 50%;
			left: 50%;
			width: 0;
			height: 0;
			border-radius: 50%;
			background: radial-gradient(circle, var(--cyan) 0%, transparent 70%);
			opacity: 0;
			transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
			transition: all 0.5s ease;
			z-index: -1;
		}

		.spec-item:hover {
			border-color: var(--accent-secondary);
			transform: translate(-2px, -2px);
			box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.3);
		}

		.spec-item:hover::before {
			width: 200%;
			height: 200%;
			opacity: 0.05;
		}

		.spec-item strong {
			display: block;
			color: var(--accent-primary);
			margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
			font-size: 1rem;
			font-weight: 700;
			text-transform: uppercase;
			letter-spacing: 0.05em;
		}

		.spec-item p {
			margin: 0;
			font-size: 0.9375rem;
			line-height: 1.6;
			color: var(--text-secondary);
		}

		.notice {
			padding: var(--space-xl);
			background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
			backdrop-filter: blur(5px);
			border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-primary);
			border-radius: 6px;
			box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(255, 0, 255, 0.1);
		}

		.notice h3 {
			color: var(--accent-primary);
			margin-top: 0;
			font-weight: 900;
		}

		.notice p {
			margin-bottom: 0;
			color: var(--text-secondary);
		}

		.cta-buttons {
			display: flex;
			gap: var(--space-lg);
			justify-content: center;
			margin-top: var(--space-xl);
		}

		@media (max-width: 768px) {
			.product-header {
				flex-direction: column;
				align-items: flex-start;
			}

			.specs {
				grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			}

			.cta-buttons {
				flex-direction: column;
				align-items: stretch;
			}
		}
	</style>
</body>
</html>
